<bold>Example</bold><linebreak/>
</para>
<para>We define our own items class based on the available <computeroutput><ref refid="classCGAL_1_1HalfedgeDS__face__base" kindref="compound" external="/home/runner/work/cgal-cn/cgal-cn/build_doc/doc_tags/HalfedgeDS.tag">CGAL::HalfedgeDS_face_base</ref></computeroutput> base class for faces. We derive the the <computeroutput>Halfedge_wrapper</computeroutput> without further modifications from the <computeroutput><ref refid="classCGAL_1_1HalfedgeDS__items__2" kindref="compound" external="/home/runner/work/cgal-cn/cgal-cn/build_doc/doc_tags/HalfedgeDS.tag">CGAL::HalfedgeDS_items_2</ref></computeroutput>, replace the <computeroutput>Face_wrapper</computeroutput> definition with our new definition, and also replace the <computeroutput>Vertex_wrapper</computeroutput> with a definition that uses <computeroutput>Point_3</computeroutput> instead of <computeroutput>Point_2</computeroutput> as point type. The result is a model for the <computeroutput><ref refid="classPolyhedronItems__3" kindref="compound">PolyhedronItems_3</ref></computeroutput> concept similar to the available <computeroutput><ref refid="classCGAL_1_1Polyhedron__items__3" kindref="compound">CGAL::Polyhedron_items_3</ref></computeroutput> class. See also there for another illustrative example.</para>
